    "docHtml": "<!-- This file has been generated using\n     the \"@coffeekraken/s-markdown-builder\" package.\n     !!! Do not edit it directly... -->\n\n<!-- body -->\n\n<!--\n/**\n* @name            01. Installation\n* @namespace       doc\n* @type            Markdown\n* @platform        md\n* @status          stable\n* @menu            Documentation           /doc/installation\n*\n* @since           2.0.0\n* @author    Olivier Bossel <olivier.bossel@gmail.com> (https://coffeekraken.io)\n*/\n-->\n\n<h1 id=\"installation\">Installation</h1>\n<p>Out stylekit works on top of <a href=\"https://postcss.org/\">PostCSS</a>. So you will need to install it first as well as the stylekit itself like so:</p>\n<s-code-example>\n   <template language=\"bash\">\n\n\nnpm i postcss @coffeekraken/s-sugarcss-plugin -D\n\n\n   </template>\n</s-code-example>\n\n<p>Then, all you need to do is to create a <code>postcss.config.js</code> file at the root of your project like so:</p>\n<s-code-example>\n   <template language=\"js\">\n\nmodule.exports = {\n  plugins: [require('@coffeekraken/s-sugarcss-plugin')],\n  // all the other plugins you want here...\n};\n\n\n   </template>\n</s-code-example>\n\n<p>You will be able now to use the stylekit in your projet.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>For informations on how to install PostCSS into your project, please refer to the <a href=\"https://postcss.org/\">PostCSS documentation</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
